A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 2 of Chapter 9 of Title 42 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to grants of pardons, paroles, and other relief, so as to provide for procedures when
3 a person is denied parole after completing certain prerequisites; to provide for a video
4 conference hearing where prospective parolees can be heard and seek information from the
5 board; to provide that the board submit written findings if the tentative parole month is
6 delayed; to provide notice to members of the board when a majority votes to deny or delay
7 release; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
9 SECTION 1.
10 Article 2 of Chapter 9 of Title 42 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
11 grants of pardons, paroles, and other relief, is amended by adding a new Code section to read
12 as follows:
13 "42-9-43.2.
14 (a) If any offender has accumulated the maximum number of credits available under any
15 performance incentive program provided by the Department of Corrections, or if such
