16 offender is serving a sentence of life imprisonment and is being considered or reconsidered
17 for parole, such offender may request:
18 (1) A video conference at least 30 days in advance of the tentative parole date with all
19 members of the board before any decision can be made on parole, in which the offender
20 has a reasonable opportunity to present information and questions to the board regarding:
21 (A) The nature of the offense, including any procedural matters relating to the
22 conviction and sentencing of such offense;
23 (B) The conduct and completion of programming while the offender was incarcerated;
24 (C) Community ties and other support for the offender;
25 (D) The victim or victim's family or other individuals that would be affected by the
26 offender's release; and
27 (E) The position of the prosecuting attorney and the court regarding the offender's case;
28 and
29 (2) Written findings of fact, including the queries provided in paragraph (1) of this
30 subsection, that provide the basis for the board's decision to deny parole or delay such
31 offender's tentative parole release month, and provide on the record:
32 (A) Any affiliates or representatives of the offender that the board contacted and
33 received information from regarding the offender's prospective release;
34 (B) Any affiliates or representatives of the victim or victims that the board contacted
35 and received information from regarding the offender's prospective release; and
36 (C) Whether such contact was made telephonically, electronically, or in person.
37 (b) In any case where three members of the board have tentatively decided to deny parole
38 or delay the tentative parole month, the other two members shall be notified of the tentative
39 decision and given 14 days to hold the decision before it is issued. During such time such
40 two members may discuss the decision with the other members of the board, and the
41 majority who tentatively decided to deny parole or delay the tentative parole month shall,
42 within their discretion, have the opportunity to change their votes.
